<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's long been known for her eye-catching style choices.</p>

<p>And Helena Bonham Carter was once again displaying her kooky fashion sense as she headed out for a stroll in north London.</p>

<p>The Crown star, 54, opted for a velvet trench coat and a mixed-print scarf as she grappled with her glasses during the outing.</p>

<p>Out and about: Helena Bonham Carter was once again displaying her kooky fashion sense as she headed out for a stroll in north London</p>

<p>Helena showed off her funky style choices by opting for a loose black velvet trench coat, teamed with a matching dress and chunky boots.</p>

<p>The actress finished her outfit with a colourful scarf that boasted a mixture of prints as she chatted to a male pal.</p>

<p>During the walk Helen struggled with adjusting her glasses as she chatted to a male pal.</p>

<p>In recent months Helena has been in a relationship with boyfriend Rye Dag Holmboe 32, and she said in late 2019 that their romance has been 'a bit of unexpected magic in my life.'</p>

<p>Off for a walk: The Crown star opted for a velvet trench coat and a mixed-print scarf as she grappled with her glasses during the outing</p>

<p>Helena shares son Billy, 16, and 12-year-old daughter Nell with her ex Tim Burton, 62.</p>

<p>The Cinderella star had a famously unconventional 13-year relationship with director Tim, which ended in 2014.</p>

<p>On finally moving on from Tim, the Enid star – who previously dated Irish actor Kenneth Branagh between 1994 and 1999 – admitted she grew tired of 'grieving' their relationship, and now leads a 'happy' life with her new boyfriend.</p>

<p>Speaking to Harper's Bazaar UK, the thespian shared: 'You break up, you grieve, you get bored of grieving. And then you finally move on.</p>

<p>'I'm very happy with someone else. It's been a bit of unexpected magic in my life.' </p>

